Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.44,0:00:09.82,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,When I must hide these burning feelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.55,0:00:13.23,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.23,0:00:14.80,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,He began moving towards \Nthe two-syllable card
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.80,0:00:16.97,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"When I" {\i0}on the first syllable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.97,0:00:18.98,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,For most players, there are only
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.98,0:00:21.89,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,seven one-syllable cards:{\i1} "Waves, \NGust, Long, All, Swift, Look, Rain."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.89,0:00:24.50,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,But in our interview, the \NMaster had this to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.78,0:00:29.00,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,There are 28 one-syllable cards for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.41,0:00:35.94,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,28 one-syllable cards?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.47,0:00:42.77,Chiha-title,A,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1700,0)}Chihaya Furu
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.04,0:01:52.09,Chiha-ep-title-poem,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(900,1000)}Moonlight,\N Clear\N and \NBright
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.04,0:01:52.09,Chiha-ep-title-verse,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(900,1000)}Verse 25
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.84,0:01:52.66,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, there \Nare 21 additional cards
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.66,0:01:56.97,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,that Master Suo can recognize \Non the first syllable?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.97,0:01:59.42,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,For example, he can hear \Nthe difference between the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.42,0:02:01.41,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"When" {\i0}in {\i1}"When I must hide"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.41,0:02:04.47,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,and the {\i1}"When"{\i0} in {\i1}"When the misty bridge"{\i0},\Nby the following syllable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.76,0:02:07.82,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,In the world of karuta, \Nwe describe this ability
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.82,0:02:09.42,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,as having excellent game sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.42,0:02:12.27,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,It would be safe to \Nassume that Master Suo
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.27,0:02:15.29,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,has the best sense of \Nall current players.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.33,0:02:18.36,Chiha-internal,All,0000,0000,0000,,But his sense is so lame.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.36,0:02:26.87,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,I feel as though my body is \Non fire with Ibuki mugwort
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.83,0:02:37.80,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,(While) some dodge the famous waves of \NTakashi shore to avoid getting wet,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.58,0:02:38.72,Chiha-internal,Suo,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I love you, Kyoko-tan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.95,0:02:42.14,Chiha-internal,Suo,0000,0000,0000,,Of all the certified readers,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.14,0:02:44.54,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,Kyoko-tan is the one who loves \Nthe Japanese language the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.36,0:02:47.13,Chiha-internal,Suo,0000,0000,0000,,The "Like" in "Like a boatsman".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.13,0:02:48.76,Chiha-internal,Suo,0000,0000,0000,,The "Like" in "Like the sound".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.23,0:02:50.62,Chiha-internal,Suo,0000,0000,0000,,They're the same word,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.28,0:02:54.41,Chiha-internal,Suo,0000,0000,0000,,but Kyoko-tan sees different \Nimages when she reads the cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.23,0:02:57.11,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,Like the sound...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.61,0:02:59.78,Chiha-internal,Suo,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I may be the only one
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.78,0:03:01.55,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,who can tell the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.52,0:03:06.68,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,He's on a completely different level.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.68,0:03:08.62,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,What are we supposed to do against him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.62,0:03:10.67,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,He must be a psychic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.67,0:03:12.34,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,He moved as soon as she \Nopened her mouth...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.34,0:03:14.57,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Still, aren't they exaggerating about
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.57,0:03:16.74,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,having 28 one-syllable cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.74,0:03:18.59,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,The human ear isn't capable \Nof differentiating
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.59,0:03:19.85,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,between those sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.85,0:03:21.13,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Chihaya-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.68,0:03:35.84,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Since the dew atop the blades of grass \Nhas been scattered by the winds,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.56,0:03:31.43,Chiha-main,Ken,0000,0000,0000,,Ooh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.43,0:03:32.56,Chiha-main,Yuu,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.17,0:03:35.33,Chiha-main,Yuu,0000,0000,0000,,The Master's so good, Bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.33,0:03:37.24,Chiha-main,Ken,0000,0000,0000,,He's so good that it's boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.24,0:03:39.99,Chiha-main,Ken,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.99,0:03:42.78,Chiha-main,Yuu,0000,0000,0000,,It's the opponent's \Nfault for being weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.78,0:03:45.33,Chiha-main,Ken,0000,0000,0000,,Bro was pretty weak when he lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.33,0:03:47.90,Chiha-main,Yuu,0000,0000,0000,,B-But Bro put up more of a fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.90,0:03:48.95,Chiha-main,Ken,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.95,0:03:49.83,Chiha-main,Yuu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.83,0:03:51.48,Chiha-main,Ken,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, stop sucking up, Yuuta!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.48,0:03:52.93,Chiha-main,Yuu,0000,0000,0000,,You should stop yapping, Kenta!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.38,0:03:53.67,Chiha-overlap,Murao,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.36,0:03:57.54,Chiha-main,Murao,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody wins in a fight between twins!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.22,0:04:01.05,Chiha-internal,Murao,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't put up a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.73,0:04:04.85,Chiha-internal,Murao,0000,0000,0000,,It's our fault for leaving \Nhim alone out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.24,0:04:09.85,Chiha-internal,Murao,0000,0000,0000,,Alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.98,0:04:15.91,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The storm will soon carry \Nme to the afterlife,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.63,0:04:13.15,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! Takemura, grade 6,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.15,0:04:14.18,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,commits a fault by \Ntouching "{\i1}The storm blasts"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.18,0:04:15.61,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,in his lower left row.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.58,0:04:17.34,Chiha-internaloverlap,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,You can't gamble like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.56,0:04:20.27,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,If you look at the Master's positioning,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.27,0:04:22.52,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,he's sacrificing his \Nmultiple-syllable cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.52,0:04:24.00,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,They can be taken for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.58,0:04:25.98,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,I have to treat "As the years" and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.98,0:04:27.81,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,"As the first" as two-syllable cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.81,0:04:30.65,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,"Would the" and "Would this"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.65,0:04:33.00,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,have to be split like one-syllable cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.60,0:04:34.92,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,How should I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.49,0:04:38.64,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,No, the real one-syllable \Ncards are the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.64,0:04:40.45,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,I can't afford to lose those.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.45,0:04:43.30,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,"Long" and "Look" will come \Ndown to the "L" sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.30,0:04:45.17,Chiha-flashback,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,The Master has an
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.17,0:04:48.26,Chiha-flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,overwhelming advantage \Nin the Master match.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.26,0:04:50.75,Chiha-flashback,Gran,0000,0000,0000,,The first opponent for a new challenger
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.75,0:04:55.10,Chiha-flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,is the pressure of sitting on that stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.00,0:04:57.52,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.30,0:05:01.00,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,So I have to visualize...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.68,0:05:04.71,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,I can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.33,0:05:10.11,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,I can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.38,0:05:12.45,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,I can do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.98,0:05:16.45,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,I can do it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.75,0:05:22.18,Chiha-main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.18,0:05:23.01,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's over!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.46,0:05:24.64,Chiha-overlap,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.46,0:05:25.18,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Master Suo was never behind
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.18,0:05:27.76,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,as he won his fourth \Nstraight Master title.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.41,0:05:27.76,Chiha-overlap,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.20,0:05:30.79,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,His strengths are simple, \Nbut consistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.79,0:05:33.19,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,How long will his streak continue?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.36,0:05:39.92,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa, visualizing only goes so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.88,0:05:43.40,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,I have to practice or my body \Nwon't know how to move...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.81,0:05:45.53,Chiha-internal,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,Against a strong opponent!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.87,0:05:53.37,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Suo-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.60,0:05:55.15,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations on your fourth victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.15,0:05:57.81,Chiha-main,B,0000,0000,0000,,Please try to graduate \Nfrom college next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.81,0:05:58.41,Chiha-main,Suo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.41,0:06:00.81,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,A little more confidence, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.81,0:06:01.25,Chiha-main,Suo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.84,0:06:04.14,Chiha-main,Ise,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations, Shinobu-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.70,0:06:07.13,Chiha-main,Shi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Coach Ise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.77,0:06:09.00,Chiha-main,Ise,0000,0000,0000,,Could you come practice
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.00,0:06:12.30,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,with the Kyoto Myojo society, \Nwhen you get a chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.30,0:06:14.52,Chiha-main,Ise,0000,0000,0000,,The other members would \Nbe thrilled to have you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.84,0:06:17.16,Chiha-main,Shi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that would be an honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.16,0:06:20.77,Chiha-main,Shi,0000,0000,0000,,Once I've gotten a little \Nstronger, I'll stop by.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.37,0:06:22.72,Chiha-main,Ise,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.32,0:06:25.86,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Stronger?  Than she already is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.86,0:06:28.16,Chiha-main,B,0000,0000,0000,,She's telling him that she won't go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.22,0:06:29.49,Chiha-main,B,0000,0000,0000,,Kyoto women are all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.37,0:06:33.70,Chiha-internal,Kita,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose I may be biased, as a coach...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.26,0:06:35.87,Chiha-flashback,Yumi,0000,0000,0000,,Please show me the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.94,0:06:40.67,Chiha-internal,Kita,0000,0000,0000,,but those were the most beautiful \Nwords I'll ever hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.54,0:06:43.67,Chiha-internal,Kita,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if it's \Ncoincidence or fate,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.10,0:06:44.12,Chiha-overlap,A,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Excuse me.  Can I take a picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:46.07,Chiha-internal,Kita,0000,0000,0000,,but the current Master and Queen
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.59,0:06:47.99,Chiha-overlap,A,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Then can you and the Master\N stand next to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.07,0:06:47.97,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,have no teacher figures.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.40,0:06:51.72,Chiha-internal,Kita,0000,0000,0000,,What a waste...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.59,0:06:55.01,Chiha-internal,Kita,0000,0000,0000,,A person who never had a teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.01,0:06:57.09,Chiha-internal,Kita,0000,0000,0000,,can't become a teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.45,0:07:05.84,Chiha-main,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my, everyone?
